1
00:00:44,336 --> 00:00:45,421
Eui-ju!

2
00:00:45,504 --> 00:00:46,839
CHAPTER 26:
YOU'RE AN OUTLIER

3
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:55,931
Are you in pain, miss?

4
00:00:56,766 --> 00:00:58,267
Are you Ms. Yeo's guardian?

5
00:00:58,350 --> 00:00:59,185
Yes.

6
00:00:59,268 --> 00:01:01,520
How long has she been sweating like this?

7
00:01:01,604 --> 00:01:04,190
-About 30 minutes.
-Does she often suffer abdominal pain?

8
00:01:04,273 --> 00:01:06,984
-I'm not sure.
-Okay.

9
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,278
Will you please wait in the waiting room?

10
00:01:09,361 --> 00:01:10,196
Is it serious?

11
00:01:10,279 --> 00:01:11,572
-Just wait for now.
-All right.

12
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:12,990
Doctor, it's an emergency.

13
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,158
Let me check you over.

14
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:15,117
It hurts.

15
00:01:15,201 --> 00:01:16,410
-It hurts here?
-Yes.

16
00:01:16,494 --> 00:01:18,162
What about here? Does it hurt a lot?

17
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:19,997
Let's take her
to the emergency treatment room.

18
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,457
Let's go.

19
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:23,000
EMERGENCY ROOM
ENTRY RESTRICTIONS

20
00:01:43,145 --> 00:01:46,398
Anyone going in there
falls under one of just two categories.

21
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:48,400
It must be serious.

22
00:01:48,984 --> 00:01:50,110
The poor thing.

23
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:52,446
"Serious"?

24
00:01:53,072 --> 00:01:55,032
HANA UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

25
00:02:24,562 --> 00:02:26,313
Is Yeo Eui-ju's guardian here?

26
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:28,607
Yes, that's me.

27
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:41,495
Mr. Ga.

28
00:02:42,663 --> 00:02:44,665
What am I going to do now, Mr. Ga?

29
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:46,375
I should've known.

30
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,377
I did wonder about

31
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,963
why I've lost my appetite
and been suffering from indigestion.

32
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:53,549
I saw a case like mine on TV.

33
00:02:53,632 --> 00:02:55,593
Acute leukemia.

34
00:02:56,552 --> 00:02:59,221
Even people who appear healthy
get struck down like this.

35
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:03,183
But if you collapse suddenly like this,
it means you don't have long to live.

36
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:05,477
I'm…

37
00:03:05,561 --> 00:03:08,397
I'm only 18 years old.

38
00:03:09,106 --> 00:03:10,482
When I became an adult,

39
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:13,360
I wanted to buy an R-rated novel
in my own name

40
00:03:14,153 --> 00:03:17,448
and load my account up with 100,000 won
at a time and read whatever I wanted.

41
00:03:18,741 --> 00:03:19,992
Mr. Ga.

42
00:03:21,619 --> 00:03:22,578
I…

43
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:26,874
I have a bad feeling about this.

44
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,876
I really think…

45
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:30,961
Are you feeling better?

46
00:03:33,255 --> 00:03:34,340
What's wrong with her?

47
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:35,466
Here you are, doctor.

48
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:36,425
Oh, dear.

49
00:03:36,508 --> 00:03:39,219
All right. Let's take a look
at your X-ray together.

50
00:03:39,845 --> 00:03:43,849
You can see here.
It's been building up for quite a while.

51
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:46,560
Not good at all.

52
00:03:46,644 --> 00:03:48,812
Why didn't you come in sooner?

53
00:03:49,772 --> 00:03:52,566
Mr. Ga, what am I going to do?

54
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:53,692
Oh, my.

55
00:03:53,776 --> 00:03:55,235
It's okay. It won't be that serious.

56
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:58,364
Mr. Ga, I don't want to die.

57
00:03:58,447 --> 00:03:59,490
Don't worry. Hush now.

58
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:00,950
-What do I do?
-They can treat you.

59
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:02,284
Please call my mom.

60
00:04:02,368 --> 00:04:04,411
They can treat you. You will be fine!

61
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:08,832
Please call my mom.

62
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,251
Is it a serious illness?

63
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:13,337
She had constipation.

64
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:19,593
Sorry?

65
00:04:22,096 --> 00:04:23,263
But…

66
00:04:24,348 --> 00:04:27,434
Can constipation cause you to pass out?

67
00:04:27,518 --> 00:04:28,936
Shouldn't you run more tests?

68
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:30,312
She was full to bursting.

69
00:04:30,396 --> 00:04:33,899
All the white you see here is stool.

70
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,362
We gave her an enema.

71
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:41,115
And this is how you look now.

72
00:04:41,198 --> 00:04:43,701
Isn't that nice and clean?

73
00:04:45,703 --> 00:04:48,038
When you get home,

74
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:49,665
why don't you try weighing yourself?

75
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:53,085
You're free to leave.

76
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:09,601
Please just leave, Mr. Ga.

77
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,980
I'll make my own way home.

78
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:14,732
Please just leave without another word.

79
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:15,649
Please.

80
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,987
Why aren't you going?

81
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:22,406
Please just leave.

82
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:23,699
Right now.

83
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:25,993
I will never get…

84
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:28,954
how you…

85
00:05:30,164 --> 00:05:31,081
always manage…

86
00:05:33,876 --> 00:05:36,170
to prove yourself to be an outlier.

87
00:05:43,427 --> 00:05:44,386
I'm off.

88
00:05:59,068 --> 00:06:00,527
Shall I just transfer?

89
00:06:02,905 --> 00:06:03,739
Oh, my.

90
00:06:03,822 --> 00:06:05,157
Eui-ju!

91
00:06:05,783 --> 00:06:07,451
-Where is she?
-Eui-ju!

92
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:09,578
-Eui-ju!
-Eui-ju!

93
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:10,829
-Eui-ju!
-I'm fine.

94
00:06:10,913 --> 00:06:12,748
-Eui-ju!
-Does it hurt a lot?

95
00:06:12,831 --> 00:06:14,416
Mom, I want to transfer.

96
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,334
Transfer?

97
00:06:18,087 --> 00:06:20,506
EPISODE 8

98
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:26,095
Why do you think
Woo-su changed his mind about filming?

99
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:28,639
He must have been blackmailed.

100
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,600
Do you know how scary the principal is?

101
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:33,268
Her expression can change in an instant.

102
00:06:33,352 --> 00:06:35,270
He's not the type to give in to blackmail.

103
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:36,897
-Right.
-Sure.

104
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,273
-Yeah.
-You got that right.

105
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:41,068
What has she got on him?

106
00:06:42,111 --> 00:06:44,029
He's home.
You'd better apologize properly.

107
00:06:44,113 --> 00:06:45,989
Okay already.

108
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:50,953
You're late. You haven't had dinner yet?

109
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:55,749
I'll go get some rice.
You can get the soup.

110
00:07:02,297 --> 00:07:03,173
Great work today.

111
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,510
Is that it?

112
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:08,470
Didn't you have something to say to him?

113
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:14,017
I'm sorry about earlier.

114
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:15,644
About what, exactly?

115
00:07:16,854 --> 00:07:18,522
Dude, can't you just accept my apology?

116
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:24,236
Well.

117
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:28,991
You know.

118
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:31,952
I'm sorry that I went behind your back

119
00:07:32,828 --> 00:07:34,955
to have you filmed
when I knew you hated it

120
00:07:37,124 --> 00:07:39,376
and brushed off your past trauma
like it was nothing.

121
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:45,174
At least you know.

122
00:07:45,257 --> 00:07:46,466
What about cutlery?

123
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,677
Right. I'll get it.

124
00:07:50,512 --> 00:07:51,388
You're so cool.

125
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:57,144
Don't you have anything to say to me?

126
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:01,148
I won't call you fruit bat
for the next month.

127
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,900
Can you just not call me that at all?

128
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:04,860
-What do you think?
-You totally can, glasses monkey!

129
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:06,153
-Jeez, you fruit bat.
-Hey!

130
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:08,739
Did you hear that? He just did it!

131
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:10,824
He said he wouldn't!

132
00:08:10,908 --> 00:08:12,201
I never pinky-promised.

133
00:08:14,578 --> 00:08:15,537
I'm not eating anymore.

134
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,207
-Why the heck am I a fruit bat?
-Suit yourself.

135
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:25,547
I thought I was done
with embarrassing myself.

136
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:40,270
Eui-ju!

137
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:41,730
So broad,

138
00:08:42,773 --> 00:08:44,024
so warm…

139
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:46,944
and so cozy.

140
00:09:28,902 --> 00:09:30,487
According to a study
on constipation in teens

141
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:34,533
and related factors,

142
00:09:35,117 --> 00:09:38,078
the top three causes of constipation are

143
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:42,124
low levels of physical activity at 43%,
excessive instant food intake at 24.6%,

144
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:43,834
and irregular sleep patterns at 16%.

145
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:47,462
I assume these contributed
to the unfortunate incident yesterday.

146
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:49,840
I'll keep that in mind.

147
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:51,425
Thank you for yesterday.

148
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:53,593
I'm not religious,
but it was a weird feeling.

149
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:57,306
I bestowed grace upon the student
who betrayed me.

150
00:10:05,897 --> 00:10:08,191
How backed up were you
that you had to go to the ER?

151
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:10,736
It's because you don't drink enough water.

152
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:13,071
Your poop gets hard like stones
and won't come out.

153
00:10:13,155 --> 00:10:14,573
What? Wait, no.

154
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:15,866
Are you okay, Eui-ju?

155
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,200
I hear you went to the ER.

156
00:10:19,578 --> 00:10:22,539
How could you hold it in
until it got that bad?

157
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,042
You're definitely a bit slow.

158
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:27,419
Oh, and thanks for yesterday.

159
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:28,378
Mr. Noh.

160
00:10:30,047 --> 00:10:32,841
What was that about yesterday?
You said you knew something.

161
00:10:34,384 --> 00:10:35,218
What?

162
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,847
You said you knew my secret.

163
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:40,724
What would I know?

164
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:47,856
I can totally see the change.

165
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:49,483
You're looking a lot better today.

166
00:10:56,615 --> 00:10:57,449
What the heck?

167
00:10:58,784 --> 00:11:00,077
Did he trick me?

168
00:11:01,787 --> 00:11:04,623
So the math teacher
hasn't spilled the beans about my novel?

169
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:11,129
Hey, Eui-ju!
Going to the ER with constipation?

170
00:11:11,213 --> 00:11:12,214
That's no big deal!

171
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:13,840
There's no need to feel embarrassed!

172
00:11:13,924 --> 00:11:15,550
Just make sure you poop properly!

173
00:11:15,634 --> 00:11:16,593
You got this, Eui-ju!

174
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:18,553
Constipation is no joke!

175
00:11:18,637 --> 00:11:20,263
All right, fine. See you!

176
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:30,732
-Oh A-rin.
-Here.

177
00:11:30,816 --> 00:11:32,192
CHAPTER 27:
LIKE A CAT, LITTLE BY LITTLE

178
00:11:32,275 --> 00:11:34,027
-Choi Yu-mi.
-Here.

179
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:35,487
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Here.

180
00:11:36,571 --> 00:11:37,989
-Choi Go-ya.
-Here.

181
00:11:38,073 --> 00:11:39,074
Choi Ji-a.

182
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:51,503
-Hong Su-min.
-Here.

183
00:11:52,129 --> 00:11:53,213
-Jeon Chae-won.
-Here.

184
00:11:53,296 --> 00:11:54,714
-Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

185
00:11:55,799 --> 00:11:57,092
-Jenny.
-Here.

186
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:01,304
Give it your all in class today.
Have a good one.

187
00:12:01,388 --> 00:12:03,140
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

188
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:04,307
Eui-ju, come with me.

189
00:12:15,444 --> 00:12:16,528
Why isn't Ji-a here?

190
00:12:17,446 --> 00:12:19,114
I don't know.

191
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:23,535
When I asked about Ji-a on day one,
you were the only one who answered.

192
00:12:23,618 --> 00:12:24,995
Want to guess how I interpreted it?

193
00:12:26,663 --> 00:12:31,960
I thought that with your help,
she might feel more positive about school.

194
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:35,338
She might even change.
That made me trust you.

195
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:41,303
I want you to step up your game
and try to help her.

196
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,638
Let's say you know
someone is waiting for you at school.

197
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:45,015
Even if you hated it,

198
00:12:45,098 --> 00:12:46,766
you'd still drag yourself here,
wouldn't you?

199
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:51,480
The thing is, the way I see it,

200
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:54,691
Ji-a is not the kind of girl
you can just go up to.

201
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,611
What I mean is, she's just like a cat.

202
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:02,699
You have to creep up to her cautiously,
little by little.

203
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:06,661
Try that, then.

204
00:13:09,331 --> 00:13:10,874
But you're getting four demerits today.

205
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,835
Are you going to betray my trust?

206
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:15,003
No, sir.

207
00:13:23,386 --> 00:13:25,639
What on earth…

208
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:30,644
Damn you, Ji-a.

209
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:33,813
Ji-a's absent again.

210
00:13:33,897 --> 00:13:34,940
Tell me about it.

211
00:13:36,066 --> 00:13:39,152
By the way, why is she always by herself?

212
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,488
I'm not sure.

213
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:44,616
Some people just prefer
keeping themselves to themselves.

214
00:13:44,699 --> 00:13:45,534
Maybe she's one.

215
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:50,956
To be honest, I find her a bit scary.

216
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:53,750
Feels like things will kick off
if I rub her the wrong way.

217
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:58,505
Come on, she's not much of a talker,
but she's not like that.

218
00:13:58,588 --> 00:14:00,507
She was in my class in tenth grade.

219
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:03,969
I remember she always picked up
a chalk that fell on the floor.

220
00:14:04,052 --> 00:14:07,013
Oh, and whereas other kids
found it a pain to do the recycling,

221
00:14:07,097 --> 00:14:09,891
she would stay behind alone
to take care of it.

222
00:14:10,809 --> 00:14:11,810
So…

223
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:15,272
There are people
who favor actions rather than words.

224
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:16,856
I think that's her style.

225
00:14:18,149 --> 00:14:19,150
Here she is now.

226
00:14:22,654 --> 00:14:23,488
There you are.

227
00:14:24,656 --> 00:14:25,699
You could've come earlier.

228
00:14:27,242 --> 00:14:29,160
Why were you late today?

229
00:14:47,721 --> 00:14:51,099
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

230
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:54,603
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

231
00:14:58,607 --> 00:15:01,026
Let's turn to page 280.

232
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:02,152
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

233
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:11,411
We're celebrating the literature month
with a poetry and art exhibition.

234
00:15:12,287 --> 00:15:14,205
Each class has to select a representative.

235
00:15:14,289 --> 00:15:16,374
Does anyone want to try writing a poem?

236
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,380
Sir, Eui-ju's your girl.

237
00:15:22,464 --> 00:15:23,798
She's an amazing writer.

238
00:15:24,382 --> 00:15:25,967
Yeah, she's always
working on some project.

239
00:15:26,051 --> 00:15:28,011
She even won
a creative writing prize last year.

240
00:15:31,306 --> 00:15:34,851
Really? Then she can be
your class representative.

241
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:36,853
Is that okay, Eui-ju?

242
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:39,356
Okay, I'll do it.

243
00:15:39,981 --> 00:15:41,858
Sir, can Go-ya help out by drawing?

244
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,151
Sounds great.

245
00:15:43,234 --> 00:15:45,403
Is that okay, Go-ya?

246
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:49,532
Sure, anything I can do to help.

247
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:53,119
Then class two will be represented by
Yeo Eui-ju and Choi Go-ya.

248
00:15:55,538 --> 00:15:56,665
Looking forward to it.

249
00:15:56,748 --> 00:15:58,792
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir. We'll do our best.

250
00:16:12,681 --> 00:16:13,973
Are you in detention for demerits?

251
00:16:15,517 --> 00:16:16,643
Yes, sir.

252
00:16:16,726 --> 00:16:18,895
I never know when I might get more.

253
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,271
So I have to work them off.

254
00:16:21,773 --> 00:16:22,899
Did you have lunch?

255
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:24,567
Yes. How about you, sir?

256
00:16:24,651 --> 00:16:25,652
I did too.

257
00:16:27,946 --> 00:16:29,072
Eui-ju.

258
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,073
Yes?

259
00:16:35,954 --> 00:16:40,417
Mr. Ga knows
you weren't filming him the other day.

260
00:16:41,584 --> 00:16:42,419
Really?

261
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:46,339
Then why is he being so hard on me?

262
00:16:50,385 --> 00:16:51,678
It must be because of his glasses.

263
00:16:52,721 --> 00:16:53,596
His glasses?

264
00:16:54,848 --> 00:16:55,807
Yes.

265
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:58,309
I had his glasses

266
00:16:58,393 --> 00:16:59,728
back when he lost them.

267
00:17:00,311 --> 00:17:01,896
You had them?

268
00:17:03,773 --> 00:17:04,607
Yes.

269
00:17:05,942 --> 00:17:07,235
Didn't he tell you?

270
00:17:07,819 --> 00:17:09,028
He never said anything.

271
00:17:09,904 --> 00:17:10,739
What the heck?

272
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:15,076
I thought he would've trashed me
to his friends for throwing them out.

273
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:19,038
Anyhow, I don't think
he's holding a grudge against you.

274
00:17:19,122 --> 00:17:20,248
So don't get too upset.

275
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:23,126
Okay. Thanks for looking out for me.

276
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:27,714
I think it's so cool
you're a published writer.

277
00:17:27,797 --> 00:17:29,758
It's nothing.

278
00:17:29,841 --> 00:17:31,968
I've just enjoyed writing poetry
since middle school.

279
00:17:32,552 --> 00:17:34,929
I started off casually
like I was writing in a diary,

280
00:17:36,014 --> 00:17:39,350
putting into words the emotions
I couldn't keep bottled up.

281
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:44,355
I had a fair share of failures
with the Spring Literary Contest

282
00:17:45,148 --> 00:17:47,317
until a literary magazine
luckily picked up my piece.

283
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,695
Of course, I still doubt myself even now,

284
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:53,823
wondering if my writing is good enough.

285
00:17:54,741 --> 00:17:55,575
Still,

286
00:17:56,201 --> 00:18:00,872
eventually, I realized that writing is
all about putting my heart into it.

287
00:18:05,335 --> 00:18:07,128
To tell the truth,

288
00:18:07,796 --> 00:18:11,174
I've written several novels.

289
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:12,717
Really?

290
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:14,761
That's so cool.

291
00:18:14,844 --> 00:18:15,845
Not at all.

292
00:18:18,139 --> 00:18:22,268
Sir, how can I write a really great novel?

293
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:33,446
Make sure each character
has their own voice.

294
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:36,699
I think that's important.

295
00:18:38,952 --> 00:18:43,373
Each character
should have their own voice?

296
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,334
Yes.

297
00:18:47,210 --> 00:18:48,586
That's so profound.

298
00:18:51,506 --> 00:18:53,508
Now, I'm really looking forward
to your submission.

299
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:54,425
Oh, come on.

300
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:23,538
You went to the snack bar?

301
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:26,332
Yeah.

302
00:19:26,416 --> 00:19:27,500
I would've gone with you.

303
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:29,043
Thank you.

304
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:31,129
Where have you been?

305
00:19:31,713 --> 00:19:34,549
Huh? I had a chat with Mr. Yoon.

306
00:19:35,341 --> 00:19:37,677
Hey, he's so amazing.

307
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:40,096
He started writing poems in middle school.

308
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,932
He had no luck
with Spring Literary Contests,

309
00:19:43,016 --> 00:19:45,310
but he got his big break
through another channel.

310
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:49,731
I'll do my best with the piece
for our exhibition.

311
00:19:49,814 --> 00:19:52,609
That way,
your brilliant picture will shine.

312
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:54,485
We'll show everyone

313
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:57,113
what an amazing artist you are.

314
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,865
Shoot, I'm so nervous.

315
00:20:03,161 --> 00:20:04,787
Should we work on a title first?

316
00:20:04,871 --> 00:20:05,830
No.

317
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:10,209
CHAPTER 28: I'M GOING TO TRY
TO UNDERSTAND IRRATIONAL NUMBERS

318
00:20:13,004 --> 00:20:15,214
FILES FOR MR. GA
REAL FILES

319
00:20:18,676 --> 00:20:19,677
Okay.

320
00:20:19,761 --> 00:20:20,720
FILES FOR MR. GA

321
00:20:23,598 --> 00:20:25,934
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

322
00:20:41,032 --> 00:20:41,991
WOO-SUUUUUUUU

323
00:20:43,993 --> 00:20:45,244
This won't do.

324
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:47,747
I'm skipping this, dang it.

325
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:49,415
Let's move on for now.

326
00:20:51,042 --> 00:20:52,168
I'm not feeling it.

327
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,419
REAL FILES

328
00:20:58,132 --> 00:20:59,467
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

329
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:07,976
JUST THEN, SOMEONE GRABBED…

330
00:21:11,396 --> 00:21:14,565
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

331
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:17,026
Why haven't you come to my place lately?

332
00:21:17,694 --> 00:21:19,195
YOON'S EYES WIDEN IN SURPRISE.
IT'S SI-ON

333
00:21:19,946 --> 00:21:21,072
I can't.

334
00:21:21,155 --> 00:21:23,116
No, I don't want to.

335
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,451
Can you pass discrete math by yourself?

336
00:21:25,535 --> 00:21:27,829
You'll flunk without my help.

337
00:21:28,663 --> 00:21:29,914
I'll figure it out by myself.

338
00:21:31,332 --> 00:21:32,333
I'll pay you.

339
00:21:35,211 --> 00:21:36,170
What?

340
00:21:36,254 --> 00:21:37,547
You need money.

341
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:39,799
I'll pay you to come to my house.

342
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:42,593
Isn't that why you go to Tae-ha's?

343
00:21:43,469 --> 00:21:44,554
It's not like that.

344
00:21:45,138 --> 00:21:46,180
Yes, it is.

345
00:21:46,264 --> 00:21:47,974
How is that punk any different from me?

346
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:49,392
Tae-ha is nothing like you.

347
00:21:50,643 --> 00:21:52,562
And how exactly is he different?

348
00:21:53,563 --> 00:21:56,482
Ultimately, he's also using money
to make you do what he wants.

349
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,570
You're poor, so instead of money, you'll
have to find another way to repay me.

350
00:22:01,195 --> 00:22:02,196
That ten million won.

351
00:22:03,281 --> 00:22:04,741
Pay me back properly.

352
00:22:08,786 --> 00:22:09,829
Fine, take it out on me.

353
00:22:10,538 --> 00:22:11,873
Go ahead, keep your pride.

354
00:22:12,415 --> 00:22:13,708
But in the end, you'll take it.

355
00:22:14,584 --> 00:22:17,003
I'm curious how much your pride is worth.

356
00:22:18,671 --> 00:22:20,214
Why are you going this far?

357
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:23,009
Do you have to bring me down like this?

358
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:25,595
Do I seem like a pushover to you?

359
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:27,889
Don't waste your breath
and come up with a number.

360
00:22:29,265 --> 00:22:31,768
You're going to regret this.

361
00:22:32,477 --> 00:22:34,103
You're really going to regret this.

362
00:22:34,604 --> 00:22:35,605
No.

363
00:22:36,272 --> 00:22:37,648
I'll never regret it.

364
00:22:37,732 --> 00:22:38,941
Not even to my dying day.

365
00:22:41,319 --> 00:22:42,779
END OF EPISODE 5

366
00:22:46,783 --> 00:22:47,909
"Save."

367
00:22:53,122 --> 00:22:53,956
FILES FOR MR. GA

368
00:22:59,796 --> 00:23:00,838
You can do it.

369
00:23:01,589 --> 00:23:02,507
Okay, Eui-ju?

370
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,217
You've got this.

371
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,844
I can't seem to stop yawning.

372
00:23:06,928 --> 00:23:08,387
I need to get home and crash.

373
00:23:08,471 --> 00:23:10,181
You'd need to eat first.

374
00:23:10,264 --> 00:23:11,682
What are we going to eat?

375
00:23:11,766 --> 00:23:13,810
No idea. I'll have to think about it.

376
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:15,436
Something crispy and warm.

377
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:18,314
-Jeez, you're so fussy.
-Crispy!

378
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:19,232
We've got some curry.

379
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:20,525
-Curry?
-Yeah, from the other day.

380
00:23:20,608 --> 00:23:21,442
You guys go ahead.

381
00:23:22,944 --> 00:23:24,737
-Where are you going?
-Library.

382
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:26,989
He's always off to the library.

383
00:23:27,657 --> 00:23:29,200
Be home in time for dinner!

384
00:23:31,994 --> 00:23:34,539
Does the school library
have anything at his level?

385
00:24:06,654 --> 00:24:08,197
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 5

386
00:24:14,245 --> 00:24:15,788
From now on,

387
00:24:15,872 --> 00:24:17,748
I'll be your personal bitch.

388
00:24:19,292 --> 00:24:20,334
This isn't like you.

389
00:24:20,418 --> 00:24:21,419
Oh yeah?

390
00:24:21,502 --> 00:24:22,378
EPISODE 5, FOR MR. GA

391
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:23,296
What am I like, then?

392
00:24:23,379 --> 00:24:25,131
You never cared about me.

393
00:24:25,214 --> 00:24:28,718
You only did a 180
after I became close to Tae-ha.

394
00:24:29,302 --> 00:24:31,304
Are you jealous or something?

395
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:33,306
Jealous?

396
00:24:34,098 --> 00:24:35,600
Me? Jealous?

397
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:41,439
Damn right I am!

398
00:24:42,315 --> 00:24:44,108
All that icy treatment was just an act

399
00:24:44,192 --> 00:24:45,526
to hide how I felt about you.

400
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,446
But seeing you with Tae-ha
is driving me crazy.

401
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,199
It's too late.

402
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,492
Get it together, Yoon!

403
00:24:54,869 --> 00:24:57,163
Without me, there's no one left for you.

404
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:58,998
You have no other choice.

405
00:24:59,081 --> 00:24:59,957
Without me,

406
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,168
you've got nothing!

407
00:25:09,217 --> 00:25:10,843
END OF EPISODE 5

408
00:25:21,312 --> 00:25:22,688
What's the matter, Mr. Ga?

409
00:25:23,648 --> 00:25:25,191
Don't you like it?

410
00:25:50,216 --> 00:25:52,718
I wrote him as an obsessive top.

411
00:25:52,802 --> 00:25:54,303
What doesn't he like about it?

412
00:26:10,152 --> 00:26:12,613
Jeez, he still has his glasses taped up.

413
00:26:15,283 --> 00:26:16,367
What are you staring at?

414
00:26:18,244 --> 00:26:21,414
I was wondering if you'd got new glasses.

415
00:26:22,456 --> 00:26:23,833
My order's not ready yet.

416
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:26,460
They must be really expensive.

417
00:26:27,128 --> 00:26:29,714
I'm sorry I couldn't buy them for you.

418
00:26:30,548 --> 00:26:31,841
Are you sorry for what happened?

419
00:26:32,842 --> 00:26:33,843
Of course.

420
00:26:35,428 --> 00:26:37,305
What about giving up on math?

421
00:26:39,932 --> 00:26:40,850
That too.

422
00:26:49,525 --> 00:26:50,693
Write how you want to.

423
00:26:53,279 --> 00:26:54,405
Sorry?

424
00:26:55,156 --> 00:26:57,491
Write your own version,
not what I tell you.

425
00:26:58,451 --> 00:26:59,744
Really?

426
00:26:59,827 --> 00:27:00,786
That's amazing.

427
00:27:00,870 --> 00:27:01,871
Is this for real?

428
00:27:10,296 --> 00:27:13,049
To tell the truth, after you caught me,

429
00:27:13,132 --> 00:27:15,468
I thought it was game over.

430
00:27:15,551 --> 00:27:17,386
I figured that was it for me.

431
00:27:18,721 --> 00:27:22,808
Why are you allowing me to write again?

432
00:27:33,069 --> 00:27:36,280
To Pythagoras, the square root of two
was an abnormal number.

433
00:27:37,865 --> 00:27:38,824
Sorry?

434
00:27:39,867 --> 00:27:41,160
What's that got to do with it?

435
00:27:41,243 --> 00:27:44,580
Back then, the only numbers
they could calculate were natural numbers.

436
00:27:44,663 --> 00:27:47,500
Anything that couldn't be expressed
as a fraction was considered irrational.

437
00:27:47,583 --> 00:27:50,669
Such numbers were to be rejected
and not even thought of.

438
00:27:52,129 --> 00:27:54,340
I get why the Pythagoreans were shaken.

439
00:27:54,924 --> 00:27:57,802
Hippasus, who discovered
the square root of two,

440
00:27:57,885 --> 00:27:59,553
died in suspicious circumstances.

441
00:28:00,763 --> 00:28:02,723
They killed him over that?

442
00:28:04,892 --> 00:28:07,436
No one knows who killed him.
It's just a theory.

443
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,564
Wow, Pythagoras was scary.

444
00:28:15,611 --> 00:28:16,946
What do irrational numbers really mean?

445
00:28:18,781 --> 00:28:20,241
It's "irrational" numbers, right?

446
00:28:21,075 --> 00:28:23,536
I believe that things
that appear irrational or illogical

447
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:25,246
still deserve our time and attention.

448
00:28:25,329 --> 00:28:29,333
I won't repeat Pythagoras's mistake
and dismiss something

449
00:28:29,417 --> 00:28:30,751
just because it seems irrational.

450
00:28:33,254 --> 00:28:35,381
Could you put that in layman's terms?

451
00:28:42,513 --> 00:28:44,557
I'm going to try to understand
irrational numbers.

452
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:20,509
Fangirling used to be my only joy in life.

453
00:29:20,593 --> 00:29:22,178
-But now…
-Are you okay?

454
00:29:22,261 --> 00:29:24,555
The fact he keeps cropping up in my mind…

455
00:29:24,638 --> 00:29:25,473
It makes me mad.

456
00:29:25,556 --> 00:29:27,433
-I don't want to think about him.
-Let's go.

457
00:29:27,516 --> 00:29:29,602
I shouldn't think about him,

458
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:31,061
but I can't help myself.

459
00:29:31,145 --> 00:29:33,898
You're into someone,
but you don't want to admit it.

460
00:29:33,981 --> 00:29:35,065
You're in denial.

461
00:29:35,149 --> 00:29:38,194
No matter how much you deny it,
you're already into him.

462
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:40,571
No. No way.

463
00:29:40,654 --> 00:29:42,114
I shouldn't even like him,

464
00:29:42,198 --> 00:29:43,324
and I just can't.

465
00:29:43,908 --> 00:29:46,577
The guy you like isn't Mr. Jung, is it?

466
00:29:47,411 --> 00:29:49,038
They've gotten really close.

467
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:49,848
Subtitle: Paul Carver
